9 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
10 That Section(s) 10–404(g) and (h) of Article – Public Utilities of the Annotated Code of
11 Maryland be renumbered to be Section(s) 10–404(h) and (i), respectively.
12 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
13 as follows:
14 Article – Public Utilities
15 10–103.
16 (b) (1) A county or municipal corporation may license taxicab drivers who
17 drive taxicabs that are based in that county or municipal corporation if, at a minimum, the
18 county or municipal corporation:
19 (I) conducts a criminal record check [and] OF EACH APPLICANT
20 FOR A LICENSE;
21 (II) CONDUCTS A driving record check of each applicant for a license;
22 AND
23 (III) REQUIRES THAT EACH APPLICANT FOR A LICENSE INCLUDE
24 IN THE APPLICATION DOCUMENTATION VERIFYING THAT THE APPLICANT
25 COMPLETED A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS TRAINING IN ACCORDANCE WITH
26 § 10–104.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
27 (2) A taxicab driver licensed by a county or municipal corporation is not
28 required to be licensed by the Commission.
29 10–104.
30 (a) (1) An applicant for a for–hire driver’s license shall:
31 (i) submit to the Commission a completed application on the form
32 that the Commission provides;

