1 (ii) state on the form that the applicant is applying for a
2 passenger–for–hire driver’s license or a taxicab driver’s license;
3 (iii) pay to the Commission an application fee set by the Commission;
4 (iv) 1. if the applicant is a Maryland driver, allow the
5 Commission access to the driver’s photograph through the Motor Vehicle Administration;
6 or
7 2. file with the application a recent photograph in a format
8 that the Commission specifies; [and]
9 (v) SUBMIT TO THE COMMISSION DOCUMENTATION VERIFYING
10 THAT THE APPLICANT COMPLETED A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS TRAINING
11 IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 10–104.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE; AND
12 (VI) apply to the Criminal Justice Information System Central
13 Repository of the Department of Public Safety and Correctional Services for a State
14 criminal history records check as provided in subsection (b) of this section.
15 10–104.1.
16 (b) The Commission may approve an applicant and issue a temporary driver’s
17 license to the applicant if:
18 (1) the applicant provides all information that the Commission requires for
19 the application, including the information specified in item (2) of this subsection; [and]
20 (2) the Commission is satisfied with the successful submission of the
21 applicant’s:
22 (i) national criminal history records check:
23 1. conducted by a consumer reporting agency as defined
24 under § 14–1201 of the Commercial Law Article or a comparable entity approved by the
25 Commission; and
26 2. that includes:
27 A. a Multi–State Multi–Jurisdiction Criminal Records
28 Database Search or a search of a similar nationwide database with validation;
29 B. a search of the Sex Offender Registry; and
30 C. a search of the U.S. Department of Justice’s National Sex
31 Offender Public website; and

4 SENATE BILL 473
1 (ii) driving record check that includes a driving history research
2 report; AND
3 (3) THE APPLICANT SUBMITS TO THE COMMISSION DOCUMENTATION
4 VERIFYING THAT THE APPLICANT COMPLETED A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS
5 TRAINING IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 10–104.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
6 10–104.2.
7 (A) AN APPLICANT FOR A LICENSE ISSUED IN ACCORDANCE WITH §
8 10–103(B) OF THIS SUBTITLE OR UNDER § 10–104, § 10–104.1, OR § 10–106 OF THIS
9 SUBTITLE OR § 10–404 OF THIS TITLE SHALL INCLUDE IN THE APPLICATION
10 DOCUMENTATION VERIFYING THAT THE APPLICANT COMPLETED:
11 (1) (I) THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION’S LEADERS
12 AGAINST HUMAN TRAFFICKING/COMBATTING HUMAN TRAFFICKING IN THE
13 TRANSPORTATION AWARENESS TRAINING; OR
14 (II) (2) ANY NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED HUMAN TRAFFICKING
15 AWARENESS TRAINING PROGRAM; AND.
16 (2) (B) A A HUMAN TRAFFICKING PREVENTION PROGRAM THAT
17 PROVIDES AWARENESS TRAINING THAT AN APPLICANT COMPLETES UNDER
18 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION MUST INCLUDE INFORMATION ON HOW TO:
19 (I) (1) RECOGNIZE POTENTIAL VICTIMS OF HUMAN
20 TRAFFICKING;
21 (II) (2) RESPOND TO AN INDIVIDUAL WHO MAY BE OR IS A
22 VICTIM OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING; AND
23 (III) (3) CONNECT AN INDIVIDUAL WHO MAY BE OR IS A VICTIM
24 OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING WITH AVAILABLE RESOURCES REPORT SUSPECTED
25 INCIDENTS OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING TO APPROPRIATE AUTHORITIES.
26 (B) (C) A LICENSED TAXICAB DRIVER, OR FOR–HIRE DRIVER, OR
27 TRANSPORTATION NETWORK OPERATOR MAY NOT BE HELD CIVILLY OR CRIMINALLY
28 LIABLE FOR REPORTING OR RESPONDING IN GOOD FAITH TO A SUSPECTED
29 INCIDENT OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING.
30 10–106.

