7 VERIFYING THAT THE APPLICANT COMPLETED A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS
8 TRAINING IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 10–104.2 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
9 (2) The Commission may renew the for–hire driver’s license by appropriate
10 endorsement on the license.
11 (c) The Commission shall keep on file with the original application of a driver a
12 complete record of:
13 (1) each for–hire driver’s license issued to the driver; and
14 (2) any renewal, suspension, and revocation of a for–hire driver’s license
15 issued to the driver.
16 10–404.
17 (b) The Commission may approve an applicant to be an operator and issue a
18 temporary transportation network operator’s license to the applicant if:
19 (1) the applicant provides all information that the Commission requires for
20 the application, including the information specified in item (2) of this subsection; [and]
21 (2) the Commission is satisfied with the successful submission of the
22 applicant’s:
23 (i) national criminal history records check:
24 1. conducted by a consumer reporting agency as defined
25 under § 14–1201 of the Commercial Law Article or a comparable entity approved by the
26 Commission; and
27 2. that includes:
28 A. a Multi–State Multi–Jurisdiction Criminal Records
29 Database Search or a search of a similar nationwide database with validation;
30 B. a search of the Sex Offender Registry; and

6 SENATE BILL 473
1 C. a search of the U.S. Department of Justice’s National Sex
2 Offender Public Website; and
3 (ii) driving record check that includes a driving history research
4 report; AND
5 (3) THE APPLICANT SUBMITS TO THE COMMISSION DOCUMENTATION
6 VERIFYING THAT THE APPLICANT COMPLETED A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS
7 TRAINING IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 10–104.2 OF THIS TITLE.
8 (c) Subject to subsection (d) of this section, the Commission may issue a
9 permanent transportation network operator’s license to an applicant [upon] ON the
10 submission of:
11 (1) a satisfactory supplemental criminal background check as set forth
12 under § 10–104(b) of this title; AND
13 (2) DOCUMENTATION VERIFYING THAT THE APPLICANT COMPLETED
14 A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS TRAINING IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 10–104.2 OF
15 THIS TITLE.
16 (G) AN APPLICANT FOR THE RENEWAL OF A TRANSPORTATION NETWORK
17 OPERATOR’S LICENSE SHALL SUBMIT TO THE COMMISSION DOCUMENTATION
18 VERIFYING THAT THE APPLICANT COMPLETED A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS
19 TRAINING IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 10–104.2 OF THIS TITLE.
20 (G) (1) THIS SUBSECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO AN INDIVIDUAL WHO:
21 (I) SUBMITTED AN APPLICATION FOR A TRANSPORTATION
22 NETWORK OPERATOR’S LICENSE ON OR BEFORE SEPTEMBER 30, 2026; AND
23 (II) COMPLETED, BETWEEN JUNE 1, 2025, AND NOVEMBER 30,
24 2026, A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS TRAINING THAT MEETS THE
25 REQUIREMENTS OF PARAGRAPHS (2) AND (3) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
26 (2) A TRANSPORTATION NETWORK COMPANY MAY NOT ALLOW AN
27 APPLICANT FOR A TRANSPORTATION NETWORK OPERATOR’S LICENSE OR THE
28 HOLDER OF A TEMPORARY OR PERMANENT TRANSPORTATION NETWORK
29 OPERATOR’S LICENSE TO PROVIDE TRANSPORTATION NETWORK SERVICES USING A
30 DIGITAL NETWORK APPLICATION UNLESS THE APPLICANT OR LICENSE HOLDER,
31 WITHIN 30 DAYS AFTER THE APPLICANT OR LICENSE HOLDER FIRST PROVIDES A
32 PREARRANGED RIDE, HAS COMPLETED:

SENATE BILL 473 7
1 (I) THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION’S LEADERS
2 AGAINST HUMAN TRAFFICKING/COMBATING HUMAN TRAFFICKING IN THE
3 TRANSPORTATION SECTOR AWARENESS TRAINING;
4 (II) ANY NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED HUMAN TRAFFICKING
5 AWARENESS TRAINING PROGRAM; OR
6 (III) ANY DIGITAL TRAINING DEVELOPED BY A TRANSPORTATION
7 NETWORK COMPANY IN CONSULTATION WITH A NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED
8 ORGANIZATION WITH EXPERTISE IN HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS TRAINING.
9 (3) A HUMAN TRAFFICKING AWARENESS TRAINING THAT AN
10 APPLICANT OR LICENSE HOLDER COMPLETES UNDER PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS
11 SUBSECTION MUST INCLUDE INFORMATION ON HOW TO:
12 (I) RECOGNIZE POTENTIAL VICTIMS OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING;
13 (II) RESPOND TO AN INDIVIDUAL WHO MAY BE OR IS A VICTIM OF
14 HUMAN TRAFFICKING; AND
15 (III) REPORT SUSPECTED INCIDENTS OF HUMAN TRAFFICKING
16 TO APPROPRIATE AUTHORITIES.
17 (4) AN APPLICANT FOR A TRANSPORTATION NETWORK OPERATOR’S
18 LICENSE OR THE HOLDER OF A TEMPORARY OR PERMANENT TRANSPORTATION
19 NETWORK OPERATOR’S LICENSE MAY NOT BE HELD CIVILLY OR CRIMINALLY LIABLE
20 FOR REPORTING OR RESPONDING IN GOOD FAITH TO A SUSPECTED INCIDENT OF
21 HUMAN TRAFFICKING.
22 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
23 October 1, 2026.
